{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0057-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Mid-Level Doc Query Helpers",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1741737600000,
  "modified": 1774988061098,
  "content": {
    "tags": [
      "c0c0c0c0-0040-0000-0000-000000000000",
      "c0c0c0c0-0085-0000-0000-000000000000"
    ],
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Writing Active Text queries in eval blocks is too verbose and requires knowledge of HTML-like structure. Users must manually construct :h3, :p, :item-ref nodes, know content paths like (:description (:content m)), use raw GUIDs instead of @item-ref, and handle :doc wrapping and concat boilerplate."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Current query (low-level)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(def modules (sort-by :name (find-items {:type \"33333333-...\"})))\n(concat [:doc]\n  (for [m modules]\n    [:doc\n      [:h3 [:item-ref (:id m) (:name m)]]\n      [:p (extract-text (nth (:description (:content m)) 1))]]))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Proposed mid-level API"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "(def modules (sort-by :name (find-items {:type @kernel-module})))\n(listing modules\n  (item-link m)\n  (first-paragraph m))"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design direction"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Mid-level: helper functions that produce Active Text, without the user needing to know the AST structure. Low-level AST construction remains available for power users."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Specific issues to address"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "@item-ref in filters"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": find-items should accept @item-ref values in filter maps, not just raw GUID strings"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": ":doc boilerplate"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": listing/for helpers should handle fragment wrapping automatically. Consider implicit fragments (tagless arrays rendered as block sequences)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Content helpers"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": item-link (linked heading from item), first-paragraph (opening text of description), summary (short text extract) — hide content.description path and AST structure"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Listing helper"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ": iterates a collection, renders body forms per item as blocks, handles concat/:doc wrapping"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Implementation notes"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Helpers are a stdlib library — pure functions returning Active Text"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "toCompactJson already handles Hob→Active Text conversion (keywords, string wrapping)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Users writing {:s expr} get double-wrapped — helpers should make this unnecessary"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Related"
        }
